    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIn my workflow, I use Neovim for editing and Visual Studio for debugging and building. I work on a large project with 128 .csproj. However, when I build the entire project, Neovim's memory usage increases significantly (up to 10 GB), forcing me to close it,ps:it doesnt happend always.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- Open neovim\r\n- Build the project => .slnf file\r\n- neovim Crash\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nKeep working\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.10\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\ni dont know\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nwindows 11\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nTerminal\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ni dont know\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nusing winget",
